cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the use of normalization techniques in deep neural networks for various tasks related to computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of normalization techniques in conditional computation, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
